Sentencas: The maximum fracture strength of Ni/8YSZ anodes exposed to several redox cycles is compared.

Sentencas: The anodes were fabricated using fine and coarse particle size powders.

Sentencas: Fine-structured powders show a 77% increase in mechanical strength after exposure to three redox cycles.
Titulo: Fracture strength of micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell anode in redox cycling experiments

Sentencas: The coarse-structured material did not produce similar results and redox cycling resulted in gradual decrease in the mechanical stability of the supports.
Titulo: Fracture strength of micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell anode in redox cycling experiments

Sentencas: The impact of redox cycling on the microstructure was evaluated using SEM.
Titulo: Fracture strength of micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell anode in redox cycling experiments

Sentencas: Fine-structured anodes tend to agglomerate leading to decreased porosity.
Titulo: Fracture strength of micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell anode in redox cycling experiments

Sentencas: Coarse anodes did not show any significant changes in microstructure while exposed to redox cycling.
Titulo: Fracture strength of micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell anode in redox cycling experiments

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance evaluated under load conditions, and after the first redox cycle, indicates a 40% improvement for the cell fabricated using a fine-structured anode powder.
Titulo: Fracture strength of micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell anode in redox cycling experiments

Sentencas: The increase in performance is believed to be due to better adhesion between the anode material and the Ni current collector.
